SIMPLE: going
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Going
<hw>Go"ing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of
moving in any manner; traveling; <as>as, the <ex>going</ex> is
bad</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Departure.</def> <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Pregnancy; gestation; childbearing.</def>
<rj><au>Crew.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <pluf>pl.</pluf> <def>Course of life; behavior; doings;
ways.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His eyes are upon the ways of man, and he seeth all his
<qex>goings</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Job xxxiv. 21.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Going barrel</b></col>. <fld>(Horology)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <cd>A barrel containing the mainspring, and having teeth on
its periphery to drive the train.</cd> <sd>(b)</sd> <cd>A device for
maintaining a force to drive the train while the timepiece is being
wound up.</cd> -- <col><b>Going forth</b></col>. <fld>(Script.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <cd>Outlet; way of exit.</cd> ⟦ldquo⟧Every <xex>going
forth</xex> of the sanctuary.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Ezek. xliv. 5.</au>
<sd>(b)</sd> <cd>A limit; a border.</cd> ⟦ldquo⟧The <xex>going
forth</xex> thereof shall be from the south to Kadesh-barnea.⟦rdquo⟧
<au>Num. xxxiv. 4.</au> -- <mcol><col><b>Going out</b></col>,
<it>or</it> <col><b>Goings out</b></col></mcol>. <fld>(Script.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <cd>The utmost extremity or limit.</cd> ⟦ldquo⟧The border
shall go down to Jordan, and the <xex>goings out</xex> of it shall be at
the salt sea.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Num. xxxiv. 12.</au> <sd>(b)</sd> <cd>Departure
or journeying.</cd> ⟦ldquo⟧And Moses wrote their <xex>goings out</xex>
according to their journeys.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Num. xxxiii. 2.</au> --
<col><b>Goings on</b></col>, <cd>behavior; actions; conduct; -- usually
in a bad sense.</cd></cs></p>

<p><ent>Going</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Going
<hw>Go"ing</hw>, <pos>p. pr.</pos> <mord>of <er>Go</er></mord>. Specif.:
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>That goes; in existence; available for present use or
enjoyment; current; obtainable; also, moving; working; in operation;
departing; <as>as, he is of the brightest men <ex>going</ex>;
<ex>going</ex> prices or rate</as>.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>Carrying on
its ordinary business; conducting business, or carried on, with an
indefinite prospect of continuance; -- chiefly used in the phrases
<col><b>a going business</b></col>, <col><b>concern</b></col>,
etc.</def> <sd>(c)</sd> <def>Of or pertaining to a going business or
concern; <as>as, the <ex>going</ex> value of a company</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Goitre</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Goiter</ent>⟦br⟧
